## üß± Overview of OSI Layers

| Layer | Name              | Function Summary                          |
|-------|-------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| 7     | Application       | End-user interface, app services          |
| 6     | Presentation      | Data format, encryption/decryption        |
| 5     | Session           | Connection management, sessions           |
| 4     | Transport         | Reliable delivery (TCP/UDP), ports        |
| 3     | Network           | IP addressing, routing                    |
| 2     | Data Link         | MAC addressing, frames, switches          |
| 1     | Physical          | Cables, NICs, bits on the wire            |

---

## üî¢ Layer-by-Layer Breakdown

### üîπ Layer 7 ‚Äì Application
- Closest to the end-user
- Interfaces directly with software (e.g., browsers, email)
- Protocols: HTTP, FTP, SMTP, DNS

### üîπ Layer 6 ‚Äì Presentation
- Data translation (syntax), encryption, compression
- Formats: JPEG, MP4, SSL/TLS

### üîπ Layer 5 ‚Äì Session
- Establishes, maintains, and ends sessions
- Examples: NetBIOS, RPC, PPTP

### üîπ Layer 4 ‚Äì Transport
- Reliable or best-effort delivery
- Flow control, segmentation
- Protocols: TCP, UDP

### üîπ Layer 3 ‚Äì Network
- Logical addressing, routing
- Devices: Routers
- Protocols: IP, ICMP

### üîπ Layer 2 ‚Äì Data Link
- Physical addressing (MAC), error detection
- Devices: Switches, bridges
- Protocols: Ethernet, PPP

### üîπ Layer 1 ‚Äì Physical
- Transmission of raw bits
- Devices: Cables, hubs, NICs
- Standards: RJ45, Fiber, Voltage levels

---

## üß† Mnemonic to Remember the OSI Layers

From **Layer 7 to 1** (Top ‚Üí Bottom):

> **"All People Seem To Need Data Processing"**

From **Layer 1 to 7** (Bottom ‚Üí Top):

> **"Please Do Not Throw Sausage Pizza Away"**

