## ‚öôÔ∏è Real Protocols & Devices Per Layer

| Layer | Example Protocols         | Example Devices             |
|-------|---------------------------|-----------------------------|
| 7     | HTTP, FTP, SMTP, DNS      | Browsers, Email Clients     |
| 6     | SSL/TLS, JPEG, MPEG       | Application Gateways        |
| 5     | NetBIOS, PPTP, RPC        | Session Managers            |
| 4     | TCP, UDP                  | Firewalls                   |
| 3     | IP, ICMP, IPSec           | Routers                     |
| 2     | Ethernet, ARP, PPP        | Switches, NICs              |
| 1     | Ethernet Cables, RF       | Hubs, Repeaters, Cables     |

---

## ‚ö†Ô∏è Why It Matters in Cybersecurity

- üîê **Layered security**: Each layer can have its own security controls.
- üïµÔ∏è‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è **Packet analysis**: Tools like Wireshark work based on OSI layers.
- üö® **Attack detection**: Helps identify where attacks occur (e.g., ARP spoofing = Layer 2, DDoS = Layer 4).

---

‚úÖ **Use the OSI model to better understand how networks function and how to defend them. Mastering it is essential for ethical hacking, penetration testing, and network troubleshooting.**
